According to a report by Intel Market Research, the India uPVC Window Market was valued at USD 1.23 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 1.33 billion in 2025 to USD 2.01 billion by 2032, registering a CAGR of 8.5% during the forecast period. The market is experiencing robust expansion, driven by rapid urbanization, rising residential and commercial construction, growing awareness of energy-efficient building materials, and increasing adoption of sustainable construction practices. Government initiatives promoting affordable housing, smart city development, and green buildings are further creating favorable conditions for the widespread adoption of uPVC windows across India.
